g.text: To deeply explore the diffusion creep mechanism, the vacancy quantity curves corresponding
to the models in Figure 5 were obtained (Figure 7). Plots of the number of vacancies versus time
during the creep deformation process are illustrated in Figure 7. For nanocrystalline materials, it is
generally considered that the generation of vacancy is one of the main causes underlying the diffusion
creep mechanism, owing to the larger volume fraction of grain boundaries in nanocrystalline
materials and the higher probability of vacancies at grain boundaries. In this study, point defects such
as vacancy were identified using Wigner–Seitz cell method by comparing the defective crystal with
a corresponding perfect crystal lattice and distinguishing a vacancy site from non-atom occupying
